Description: Spoke Intelligence Network or SpokeIntel is the new source for timely, relevant and comprehensive information on industries
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Spoke Intelligence Network or SpokeIntel is the new source for timely, relevant and comprehensive information on industries, industry trends, companies and people— designed from the ground up to meet the needs of business managers, sales, and research professionals. Launching with an initial database of over 20,000 entities across multiple industries, SpokeIntel helps drive businesses forward with its robust crowd-sourced data gathering model, paired with automatically-updated enterprise-specific news. Business professionals turn to Spoke in search of the latest company information, including executive profiles, company milestones, industry trends, news, blog posts, and much more. VBProfiles also allows business professionals to create user-friendly profiles of companies and people in a smooth and organized process that replaces existing inefficient data gathering techniques. Profiles are shared with the community at large, including peers, partners and industry experts – all able to interact and collaborate to create relevant insights about people, companies, industries and trends. What makes us different? The Spoke Intelligence Network provides a 360 degree view of an industry, industry trends, a company and its people from all the information available on the internet — no more spending hours Googling for all the different information you need on a company. Ultimately such a view across thousands of businesses enables professionals to derive insights and drive business around an industry, a trend, a company and people. Most importantly, The Spoke Intelligence Network is community-based. We believe that information on the Internet shouldn’t be simply limited to what people publish about themselves. We envisioned a collaborative space where communities can respectfully interact around companies and people outside the control of those companies and people. The Spoke Intelligence Network will become the premier network for this kind of vibrant community. We are curating information by giving the community at large the power to update profiles and provide insights. We have created a moderation platform to provide enough oversight to ensure that community-provided content is appropriate. Our focus is business information, so this will not be the venue for airing customer support issues or maligning someone’s reputation. We are doing this in partnership with companies and individuals. In compliance with our privacy policy, individuals are able to opt-out of their profile at any time. And, is doesn’t stop there. We’re regularly aggregating additional third-party information. Over time our profiles will continue to evolve with a current mix of community-supplied and third-party relevant public information.
Industry Groups: Community and Lifestyle, Content and Publishing, Data and Analytics, Information Technology, Media and Entertainment, Software

Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Founded in 1997, Specific Impulse specializes in leveraging the power of information architecture to serve the sales, marketing, and eBusiness needs of forward-thinking companies. Through their consulting division, they offer a full range of professional web services in user experience design, information architecture, web development, web hosting, and web/IT. Specific Impulse is dedicated to developing web solutions that reduce costs, increase productivity, drive sales, and dramatically improve business execution. In 2000, when Software-as-a-Service was in its infancy (the same year SalesForce.com was introduced), Specific Impulse launched StageOne™, a powerful hosted control panel for managing virtually any web site content and business information. Using StageOne, companies can manage all their business processes, information sharing, sales intelligence, customer relationship management, and eMarketing needs, without requiring IT hand-holding and without staff needing to be trained in HTML or other web technologies. Easily configured and based on proven principles of information architecture, StageOne is designed to power complete eBusiness solutions. You can manage and track everything from business processes and information management to document and content management. StageOne also includes many eMarketing and eSales components, from personalized email campaigns and web site visitor registration to customer relationship management. For IT organizations, StageOne offers a powerful collaborative application development environment, built on principles of information architecture. An early member of the Allaire partner program, they built StageOne on the robust and scalable ColdFusion Java application server (now owned by Adobe). StageOne supports traditional database-driven development, AJAX/RIA and Flash MX. But StageOne is also offered on a SaaS model, and supports PHP, ASP.Net, and Java applications through web services and an XML layer. Today, through their StageOne Developers Alliance program, ColdFusion developers and Web/IT departments can rapidly build their own solutions on the StageOne platform.

Full Description: Global Zero is the international movement for the elimination of all nuclear weapons. Its members understand that the only way to eliminate the nuclear threat – including proliferation, nuclear terrorism and humanitarian catastrophe – is to stop the spread of nuclear weapons, secure all nuclear materials and eliminate all nuclear weapons: global zero. The movement combines cutting-edge policy development and direct dialogue with governments with public outreach, including media, online and grassroots initiatives to make the elimination of nuclear weapons an urgent global imperative.   Since its launch in Paris in December 2008, it has grown to include 300 world leaders and half a million citizens worldwide; hosted four Global Zero Summits and numerous regional conferences; built an international student movement with more than 175 campus chapters in 29 countries; produced an acclaimed documentary, Countdown to Zero, with the team behind An Inconvenient Truth; launched cutting-edge international campaigns in key countries; and produced compelling, high-production videos to reach millions of people worldwide with an empowering call to action.

Industries: Finance, Financial Services, FinTech, Mobile Payments, Personal Finance
Description: Munee is a secure digital wallet that allows you to donate to the homeless and make everyday purchases using QR code technology.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Munee is a secure digital wallet and payment platform that uses QR code technology instead of emails and phone numbers to easily send/receive money, shop and donate. The team at Munee imagines a world where paying for things is easy and safe. We offer lower transaction rates, instant deposits to vendors and easy payments without needing emails, phone numbers, or credit cards at point of sale. Additionally, businesses and retailers need no additional hardware to start accepting payment from customers. With the current state of security and payments, consumers are becoming more conscious about how and where they use and store their credit card information. Nearly every online retailer requires a customer to save their payment details on the same platform used for purchasing. This creates a security risk in and of itself. Even Apple Pay and NFC payments can be compromised because the data is sent to and from the user's device. With Munee, we're providing an alternative way to pay for things--a secure digital wallet. By separating the consumer's payment method from the retailers and online platforms, the consumer is given more security and control. Using QR codes and Stripe as our processor, customers store their cards in the app (actually it's a reference to the card) and can immediately start using it to checkout at verified Munee merchants both online and offline. By simply scanning QR codes to checkout, Munee not only creates a safer method of payment but it’s much faster than any other payment platform available. From a business standpoint, we offer a frictionless and equipment-less way to accept Munee, including lower transaction fees and instant deposits (currently for U.S. based businesses).
